featured_reviews.review_id:
It is a small two stories mosque, situated tight behind the ladka bazar market. Usually people say its on the back side of the Times of India office, Airoli. Office people from Mindspace and Reliable plaza come here for praying Friday (Jumma) prayers. There are 2 timings for friday prayer one is at 1:30 AM and second is at 2:30 AM, the timings are subjected to change.
The 1:30 prayer gets a little crowded as most people attend this timings. Try to come prepared with wuduh as the queues may get a bit longer on Fridays. If you have time try to go to the Airoli Jamma masjid, which is much bigger and spacious.
